abstract: >
  Chrono-Tensorial Flux Calculus (CTFC) is a general mathematical and computational
  framework for modeling spatiotemporal systems with non-Markovian memory,
  spatial flux interactions, and evolving covariance geometry.
  CTFC treats covariance matrices as trajectories on a flux-deformed manifold,
  introducing chrono-operators such as flux-weighted derivatives, integral memory,
  curvature surrogates, and flux-scaled spectral modes.
  The framework provides both a continuous geometric theory and a stable
  discrete-time realization (CTFC≈), enabling interpretable, bounded, and
  reproducible analysis of complex dynamical systems.
  Applications include financial markets, neural data, physical systems,
  and any domain where temporal correlation geometry evolves over time.

