  abstract: >
    We introduce Chrono-Tensorial Flux Calculus (CTFC), a unified geometric
    framework for spatiotemporal representation learning that integrates
    temporal memory, spatial flux interactions, and curvature of evolving
    covariance structures. CTFC defines a family of chrono-operators derived
    from Volterra-type memory kernels and tensor contractions, providing
    bounded and interpretable invariants. A stable discrete-time realization
    (CTFC≈) enables robust empirical application to real-world systems such
    as financial markets and neural data.

